    Receive your money transfer in a variety of ways

    Knowing money is on its way is a good feeling. Whether you need money because your flight was cancelled, for an emergency repair, or you’re simply the recipient of a very nice birthday gift, Western Union makes it easy to receive money in a variety of ways. Whatever the occasion, receiving money from abroad or in the UK. is not only a lifesaver — it’s a reminder that the world isn’t nearly as big as it felt a few minutes ago.

    • Receive money to your bank account

      Your loved ones can send money directly to billions of bank accounts1. Check if you’ve received the money transfer using digital or online banking, online at westernunion.com, or with the Western Union® app.

    • Receive money transfers directly to your mobile wallet

      In selected countries, you can receive money directly to your mobile wallet1.

    Frequently asked questions about receiving money from abroad

    How will I know if my money is ready to collect?

    Simply locate the ‘Tracking’ link on westernunion.com or the Western Union® app. Type the sender’s name and MTCN then you will see an update on the status of your transfer.

    How do I receive money with Western Union without a bank account?

    You can easily pick up cash at one of hundreds of thousands of agent locations around the world. Simply take your MTCN (tracking number) and valid ID to collect your money. 

    Please have these on hand:

      • The sender’s full name (first, middle, and last name)
      • The country where the money was sent from
      • The approximate amount that was sent
      • The unique number of the transaction (MTCN)
      • Your government-issued identification document(s) as required

    The following documents are accepted in the UK:

      • Current signed passport
      • Current full driving licence (EU) and provisional licence (UK only)
      • National identity card (EU only with the exception of UK)
      • EU residency card
      • Emergency/Temporary passport, Emergency travel documents
      • Ships passport
